ach GA. T1, T2 mapping and extracellular volume fraction (ECV): application, value and further perspectives in myocardial inflammation and cardiomyopathies. <em>Rofo</em> 2015;187(9):760–770.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1055/s-0034-1399546">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26098250/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=T1%2C+T2+mapping+and+extracellular+volume+fraction+%28ECV%29%3A+application%2C+value+and+further+perspectives+in+myocardial+inflammation+and+cardiomyopathies&amp;author=FC+Roller&amp;author=S+Harth&amp;author=C+Schneider&amp;author=GA+Krombach&amp;publication_year=2015&amp;journal=Rofo&amp;pages=760-770&amp;doi=10.1055%2Fs-0034-1399546&amp;pmid=26098250">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">12.</div><div id="r12" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Moon JC, Messroghli DR, Kellman P, et al. Myocardial T1 mapping and extracellular volume quantification: a Society for Cardiovascular Magnetic Resonance (SCMR) and CMR Working Group of the European Society of Cardiology consensus statement. <em>J Cardiovasc Magn Reson</em> 2013;15:92. <a href="https://jcmr-online.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/1532-429X-15-92">https://jcmr-online.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/1532-429X-15-92</a>. Published October 14, 2013.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1186/1532-429X-15-92">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Myocardial+T1+mapping+and+extracellular+volume+quantification%3A+a+Society+for+Cardiovascular+Magnetic+Resonance+%28SCMR%29+and+CMR+Working+Group+of+the+European+Society+of+Cardiology+consensus+statement&amp;author=JC+Moon&a